verses.text_plain: And Jacob lifted up his eyes, and looked, and, behold, Esau came, and with him four hundred men. And he divided the children unto Leah, and unto Rachel, and unto the two handmaids.
verses.verse_html: 1And Jacob lifted up his eyes, and looked, and, behold, Esau came, and with him four hundred men. And he divided the children unto Leah, and unto Rachel, and unto the two handmaids.

verses.text_plain: And he put the handmaids and their children foremost, and Leah and her children after, and Rachel and Joseph hindermost.
verses.verse_html: 2And he put the handmaids and their children foremost, and Leah and her children after, and Rachel and Joseph hindermost.

verses.text_plain: And he passed over before them, and bowed himself to the ground seven times, until he came near to his brother.
verses.verse_html: 3And he passed over before them, and bowed himself to the ground seven times, until he came near to his brother.

verses.text_plain: And Esau ran to meet him, and embraced him, and fell on his neck, and kissed him: and they wept.
verses.verse_html: 4And Esau ran to meet him, and embraced him, and fell on his neck, and kissed him: and they wept.

verses.text_plain: And he lifted up his eyes, and saw the women and the children; and said, Who are those with thee? And he said, The children which God hath graciously given thy servant.
verses.verse_html:
5And he lifted up his eyes, and saw the women and the children; and said, Who are those with thee? And he said, The children which God hath graciously given thy servant. ▼
▼ with…: Heb. to thee

footnotes.body_html: ▼ with…: Heb. to thee

verses.text_plain: Then the handmaidens came near, they and their children, and they bowed themselves.
verses.verse_html: 6Then the handmaidens came near, they and their children, and they bowed themselves.

verses.text_plain: And Leah also with her children came near, and bowed themselves: and after came Joseph near and Rachel, and they bowed themselves.
verses.verse_html: 7And Leah also with her children came near, and bowed themselves: and after came Joseph near and Rachel, and they bowed themselves.

verses.text_plain: And he said, What meanest thou by all this drove which I met? And he said, These are to find grace in the sight of my lord.
verses.verse_html:
8And he said, What meanest thou by all this drove which I met? And he said, These are to find grace in the sight of my lord. ▼
▼ What…: Heb. What is all this band to thee?

footnotes.body_text: ▼ What…: Heb. What is all this band to thee?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ What…: Heb. What is all this band to thee?

verses.text_plain: And Esau said, I have enough, my brother; keep that thou hast unto thyself.
verses.verse_html:
9And Esau said, I have enough, my brother; keep that thou hast unto thyself. ▼
▼ keep…: Heb. be that to thee that is thine

footnotes.body_text: ▼ keep…: Heb. be that to thee that is thine
footnotes.body_html: ▼ keep…: Heb. be that to thee that is thine

verses.text_plain: And Jacob said, Nay, I pray thee, if now I have found grace in thy sight, then receive my present at my hand: for therefore I have seen thy face, as though I had seen the face of God, and thou wast pleased with me.
verses.verse_html: 10And Jacob said, Nay, I pray thee, if now I have found grace in thy sight, then receive my present at my hand: for therefore I have seen thy face, as though I had seen the face of God, and thou wast pleased with me.

tokens.text: Nay, I pray thee, if now I have found
and thou wast pleased with me

verses.text_plain: Take, I pray thee, my blessing that is brought to thee; because God hath dealt graciously with me, and because I have enough. And he urged him, and he took it.
verses.verse_html:
11Take, I pray thee, my blessing that is brought to thee; because God hath dealt graciously with me, and because I have enough. And he urged him, and he took it. ▼
▼ enough: Heb. all things

footnotes.body_html: ▼ enough: Heb. all things

verses.text_plain: And he said, Let us take our journey, and let us go, and I will go before thee.
verses.verse_html: 12And he said, Let us take our journey, and let us go, and I will go before thee.

verses.text_plain: And he said unto him, My lord knoweth that the children are tender, and the flocks and herds with young are with me: and if men should overdrive them one day, all the flock will die.
verses.verse_html: 13And he said unto him, My lord knoweth that the children are tender, and the flocks and herds with young are with me: and if men should overdrive them one day, all the flock will die.

tokens.text: with me: and if men should overdrive

verses.text_plain: Let my lord, I pray thee, pass over before his servant: and I will lead on softly, according as the cattle that goeth before me and the children be able to endure, until I come unto my lord unto Seir.
verses.verse_html:
14Let my lord, I pray thee, pass over before his servant: and I will lead on softly, according as the cattle that goeth before me and the children be able to endure, until I come unto my lord unto Seir. ▼
▼ according…: Heb. according to the foot of the work, etc., and according to the foot of the children

footnotes.body_text: ▼ according…: Heb. according to the foot of the work, etc., and according to the foot of the children
footnotes.body_html: ▼ according…: Heb. according to the foot of the work, etc., and according to the foot of the children

verses.text_plain: And Esau said, Let me now leave with thee some of the folk that are with me. And he said, What needeth it? let me find grace in the sight of my lord.
verses.verse_html:
15And Esau said, Let me now leave with thee some of the folk that are with me. And he said, What needeth it? let me find grace in the sight of my lord. ▼
▼ leave: Heb. set, or, place
 , ▼
▼ What…: Heb. Wherefore is this?

footnotes.body_html: ▼ leave: Heb. set, or, place
▼ What…: Heb. Wherefore is this?

verses.text_plain: So Esau returned that day on his way unto Seir.
verses.verse_html: 16So Esau returned that day on his way unto Seir.

verses.text_plain: And Jacob journeyed to Succoth, and built him an house, and made booths for his cattle: therefore the name of the place is called Succoth.
verses.verse_html:
17And Jacob journeyed to Succoth, and built him an house, and made booths for his cattle: therefore the name of the place is called Succoth. ▼
▼ Succoth: that is, Booths

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Succoth: that is, Booths

verses.text_plain: And Jacob came to Shalem, a city of Shechem, which is in the land of Canaan, when he came from Padan–aram; and pitched his tent before the city.
verses.verse_html:
18And Jacob came to Shalem, a city of Shechem, which is in the land of Canaan, when he came from Padan–aram; and pitched his tent before the city. ▼
▼ Shechem: Gr. Sychem

verses.text_plain: And he bought a parcel of a field, where he had spread his tent, at the hand of the children of Hamor, Shechem’s father, for an hundred pieces of money.
verses.verse_html:
19And he bought a parcel of a field, where he had spread his tent, at the hand of the children of Hamor, Shechem’s father, for an hundred pieces of money. ▼
▼ Hamor: Gr. Emmor
 , ▼
▼ pieces…: or, lambs

verses.text_plain: And he erected there an altar, and called it El–elohe–Israel.
verses.verse_html:
20And he erected there an altar, and called it El–elohe–Israel. ▼
▼ El–elohe–Israel: that is God the God of Israel

footnotes.body_text: ▼ El–elohe–Israel: that is God the God of Israel
